galary.title: Better Together
galary.description: When words become unclear, I shall focus with photographs. When images become inadequate, I shall be content with silence.

galary.title: Generations
galary.description: I tend to think of the act of photographing, generally speaking, as an adventure. My favorite thing is to go where I have never been.

galary.title: Days Together
galary.description: I tend to think of the act of photographing, generally speaking, as an adventure. My favorite thing is to go where Ive never been.

galary.title: Moment By Moment
galary.description: It is through living that we discover ourselves, at the same time as we discover the world around us.

galary.title: Gather Together
galary.description: If I have any message worth giving to a beginner it is that there are no shortcuts in photography.

galary.title: Home is with you
galary.description: The camera is an instrument that teaches people how to see without a camera.

galary.title: Family is Forever
galary.description: Your first 10,000 photographs are your worst.

galary.title: Days at Home
galary.description: Landscape photography is the supreme test of the photographer and often the supreme disappointment.

galary.title: Together as Family
galary.description: The whole point of taking pictures is so that you dont have to explain things with words.

galary.title: A Love Like Ours
galary.description: There is nothing worse than a sharp image of a fuzzy concept.

galary.title: The (Last Name) Family
galary.description: The eye should learn to listen before it looks.

galary.title: 2020 with the Wolfes
galary.description: For me, the subject of the picture is always more important than the picture.

galary.title: This Is Us
galary.description: A photograph is an opportunity to keep a moment forever.

galary.title: Days with Dad
galary.description: To photograph: it is to put on the same line of sight the head, the eye and the heart.

galary.title: Moments with Mom
galary.description: You donâ€™t take a photograph, you make it.

galary.title: Taking pictures is savoring life intensely, every hundredth of a second.
Siblings & Forever Friends
galary.description: I guess I have shot about 40,000 negatives and of these I have about 800 pictures I like.

galary.title: My Brother and Me
galary.description: To me, it is better to guess at how something works, experiment, fail, guess again, fail, and keep repeating that process over and over again until you either figure it out or you discover a multiplicity of other cool tricks along the way.

galary.title: Two of a Kind (great for siblings)
galary.description: You dont make a photograph just with a camera. You bring to the act of photography all the pictures you have seen, the books you have read, the music you have heard, the people you have loved.

galary.title: Ties That Bind
galary.description: No, you dont shoot things. You capture them. Photography means painting with light. And thats what you do. You paint a picture only by adding light to the things you see.

galary.title: Adventures with (Pet Name)
galary.description: The earth is art, the photographer is only a witness.

galary.title: On This Day
galary.description: Photographers deal in things which are continually vanishing and when they have vanished there is no contrivance on earth which can make them come back again.

galary.title: To Have and to Hold
galary.description: What I like about photographs is that they capture a moment thats gone forever, impossible to reproduce.

galary.title: Where We Begin
galary.description: To the complaint, There are no people in these photographs, I respond, There are always two people: the photographer and the viewer.

galary.title: Our Best Day
galary.description: Photograph: a picture painted by the sun without instruction in art.
